SIMPLE: unroll
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unroll
<hw>Un*roll"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>roll</ets>.]</ety> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>unrol</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To open, as what is rolled or convolved; <as>as, to
<ex>unroll</ex> cloth; to <ex>unroll</ex> a banner</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To display; to reveal.</def>
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To remove from a roll or register, as a
name.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If I make not this cheat bring out another . . . let me be
<qex>unrolled</qex> and my name put in the book of virtue!</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Un-Romanized</ent>⟦br⟧
